textAfterTable: 8736 Shigehisa           Discovered 1997 Jan. 9 by T. Kobayashi at Oizumi. Osao Shigehisa (b. 1936) has actively observed variable stars since 1952. An enthusiastic recorder of the activities of Japanese amateur astronomers, he played an important role in compiling a History of Amateur Astronomy in Japan in 1987, as well as a sequel in 1994.
